This public toilet is clearly not for everybody desperate to spend a penny.

The local council has been flooded with complaints from larger locals who say they are unable to get through the 20-inch doors to access the facility.

Authorities in the city of Chengdu in southwest China's Sichuan province, said they decided to install the toilet there more than 20 years ago because of an urgent need for more public facilities.

